Math.Equation

Class Token

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Equation.Token

  • public class Token
extends java.lang.Object
    A single item from an equation String. Example: "sin(x+2)" yields the tokens {"sin":FUNC, "(":LPAR, "x":VAR, "+":OPER, "2":NUM, ")":RPAR}.

    • Method Detail

      • isConst

        public boolean isConst()
        Used to determine if a Node based on a token should be a FinalNode or a Node (in this case, it's the former).
        Returns:
        True if TYPE is a NUM or VAR or ARGS.

      • isGroup

        public boolean isGroup()
        Used to determine if a //Node based on a token should be a FinalNode or a Node (in this case, it's the latter). Also used to distinguish between functions / groups and operators.
        Returns:
        True if TYPE is a GROUP or FUNC.

      • isOper

        public boolean isOper()
        Used to distinguish between functions / groups and operators.
        Returns:
        True if TYPE is a OPER.

      • isUni

        public boolean isUni()
        Used to figure out if a node based off this is the "master node".
        Returns:
        True if TYPE == NULL and VAL == "E".

      • priority

        public int priority()
        Used to figure out which operators come before others in the "order of operations". Parentheses are handeled seperately. if isUni(), priority is 4.

        else if TYPE is FUNC or GROUP, priority is 3.

        else if TYPE is OPER: +,- == 0, *,/ == 1,and ^ == 2.

        else priority is -1.

        Returns:
        The priority.

        A String representation corresponding to the VAL and the TYPE of the Token.
